@node "MesLev" "Level Messages"

@{b}Level Messages@{ub}

These are messages you get when entering a level for the first time that
indicate either a unique level, or that something interesting has been
created on that level.

@{b}You feel excited.@{ub}
     Somewhere on this level is a large monster nest (a room full of
     critters, frequently harder than level, usually with a trapped
     door so they can get out and swarm you).

@{b}You feel really excited.@{ub}
     About half the level is a really scary monster vault, usually filled
     with Emperor liches. It also probably contains at least a couple of
     artifacts. I've lost powerful game winners to this level.

@{b}You feel an intense tension.@{ub}
     This will only happen once, and only fairly deep in the Caverns of
     Chaos. The battle bunny level.

@{b}You feel a surge of power.@{ub}
     An artifact is lying around somewhere on the level (but probably not
     unguarded). This no longer occurs in the infiinite dungeon.

@{b}You shudder.@{ub}
     This one is fairly rare. There is a special trap room on the level
     (this is a room in which much (more than half) of the floor is trapped,
     not a good place to hang out unless you've found them all and just love
     being cruel to things that insist on following you around). If one of
     the traps is of the fireball variety, be very careful about what else
     is in the room with you.

@{b}The air of this level is filled with a strange smell.@{ub}
     Only in the Caverns of Chaos; somewhere on the level the si can be
     found (always before Dwarftown). It sits on a trap, so kick it aside
     before picking it up (if possible).

@{b}This level somehow seems to be removed from the rest of the world.@{ub}
     Another unique level in the Caverns of Chaos. This is where
     kitty-karma catches up with you; the realm of the Master Cat.

@{b}You go down the staircase...the stairs are very long!!!@{ub}
     The theory is that the game was just taking too long to generate the
     level, and so Thomas had it make the excuse that the stairs were long,
     and so it was taking a while to get there. Nothing special has been
     noted about the level generated after one of these messages.

@{b}You feel like you did something very stupid.@{ub}
     This only occurs in the infinite dungeon, and only when the level you
     just left had an artifact on it that you left behind. It's gone the
     way of the level, although could be randomly generated again.

@{b}The chaos level in the infinite dungeon@{ub}
     This is a unique level in the infinite dungeon; it is very colorful
     and contains a Chaos artifact and its guardian. Once you leave the
     level, it and all of its contents will vanish and be unavailable for
     the duration of the game.

@endnode

