@{b}You hear a pained high-pitched screech in the distance.@{ub}
     A monster was hit by a spear/arrow trap.

@{b}You hear a painful bark in the distance.@{ub}
     A monster was hit by a spear/arrow trap.

@{b}You hear a painful hiss in the distance!@{ub}
     A hissing monster was hit by a spear/arrow trap.

@{b}You hear a thudding sound!@{ub}
     Something just softened the fall of a stone block trap.

@{b}You notice a slurping sound in the distance.@{ub}
     A monster just excreted a web.

@{b}You hear a ripping sound.@{ub}
     Something just tore through a web.

@{b}You hear the sound of toppling stones.@{ub}
     Something just triggered the crumbling walls around some type of nest.

@{b}You suddenly feel dizzy.@{ub}
     Something just tried to teleport to your location, but got bounced
     away because you were in the way. Presumably the monsters get dizzy
     for a moment when you try to teleport to their location, too.

@{b}You hear a burping sound.@{ub}
     A monster spawned another of its kind.

@{b}You hear a popping sound.@{ub}
     A monster duplicated itself (difference from spawning: the monsters
     hit points are temporarily halved). (Is this still accurate?)

@{b}You hear a distant "Hurumph!"@{ub}
     There's a Dorn Beast on the level.

@{b}You hear "Thumb"@{ub}
     There's a creature so large it's very steps cause this reverberation
     (for native English folks--think of a resonant "thump" that keeps
     echoing). Probably a Titan.

@{b}You hear a horrible unearthly wail in the distance!@{ub}
     You're on the Banshee level. Don't listen too closely.

@{b}You hear the clicking of many small feet!@{ub}
     There's an ant hole on the level.

@{b}You hear clicking sounds!@{ub}
     An ant just crawled out of the ant hole.

@{b}You hear an evil hissing and something large crawling about the ground!!!@{ub}
     The Queen has left the ant hole.

@{b}You hear buzzing sounds.@{ub}
     There's a bee hive on the level, and another bee just left the hive.

@{b}You sense strange vibrations.@{ub}
     You killed a hive monster, and the level is trembling with the hive's
     fury.

@{b}You sense a certain tension.@{ub}
     There's a monster pit (smaller than a nest--see level sounds--whose
     inhabitants are of typical strength for that level) on the level.

@{b}You sense a pious aura.@{ub}
     There's an altar on the level.

@{b}You hear someone counting money.@{ub}
     There's a shop on the level.

@{b}You hear the clinking of coins.@{ub}
     There's a shop on the level.

@{b}You hear someone cursing shoplifters.@{ub}
     There's a shop on the level.

@{b}You hear the chime of a bell.@{ub}
     There's a shop on the level.

@{b}You hear splashing sounds.@{ub}
     There's a pool on the level.

@{b}You hear the wind howling.@{ub}
     There's an old forge on the level.

@{b}You hear the ecstatic cries of a large crowd!@{ub}
     You're on the Arena level.

@{b}You sense imminent danger...@{ub}
     An out-of-depth monster was created or the danger factor of the level
     has increased (read a scroll of peace to undo the latter), or
     perhaps both.

