@node "Rumour" "I Heard The Other Day..."

@{b}Rumor & Truth@{ub}

Each rumor, followed by my interpretation of it or its truth.

@{b}A sharp axe is easier to wield than a sharp wit.@{ub}

@{b}All roads lead to chaos, in the end.@{ub}
     No matter which alignment path you choose, you'll end up at the gate
     or as a chaotic blob.

@{b}Always consider the consequences of yer deeds lest ye be surprised.@{ub}
     Think before you act, because others will react, especially the gods.

@{b}Always watch your back!@{ub}
     Don't let yourself get surrounded.

@{b}An anvil is nothing more than an oversized ingot of iron.@{ub}
     And it will rust just like one, too.

@{b}Be as resistant as you can.@{ub}
     Collect resistances for your own sake.

@{b}Being light as a feather makes you very rifty.@{ub}
     The rift is much safer if you are not burdened.

@{b}Care for more intelligent monsters.@{ub}

@{b}Don't believe everything *they* say.@{ub}
     Not all rumors are true!

@{b}Dragons want items made from their hide back.@{ub}
     In fact they get downright violent about seeing their skins worn by
     others.

@{b}Eating a demon daisy will make you a demon lover.@{ub}
     False, it'll just make you sick/poisoned.

@{b}Feeding rust monsters is costly but definitely worth it.@{ub}
     If you need to get away, give them some metal to munch on.

@{b}Gift shops are overpriced, unless you use a five finger discount.@{ub}
     The gift shop is overpriced, and theft is the only way to get
     everything you might want.

@{b}If you are doomed, this will be the last fortune you ever read.@{ub}
     It's that hard to survive when doomed. It's doomed, after all.

@{b}If you eat the heart of a Dragon, you will share in its strength.@{ub}
     As long as you interpret its strength as its special releation to
     certain elements. Eat dragon corpses to gain their resistances.

@{b}If you lick a Karmic Lizard, you can get high.@{ub}
     Or at least higher luck; but you have to eat it, too.

@{b}In the land of eternal darkness, light must come from within.@{ub}

@{b}It takes an iron stomach to eat black dragon steak.@{ub}
     So if you eat one, you must have an iron stomach (resistant to acid).

@{b}Join DARK (*D*ragons *a*gainst *r*easonable *k*illing).@{ub}

@{b}Living sacrifices are the most valuable of all.@{ub}
     The gods really like living sacrifices, but more than artifacts?

@{b}Look for strange items.@{ub}
     Because they are quite helpful in several circumstances.

@{b}MADE: Mindcrafters Against Drunken Explorers@{ub}

@{b}Note: Don't forget to throw all the poisoned cookies away.@{ub}

@{b}Quidquid latine dictum sit, altum viditur.@{ub}
     Wow, that sounds impressive. I wonder what it means. :^)

@{b}Remember to write something on this cookie.@{ub}

@{b}Rifts are deep.@{ub}
     Otherwise they'd be called cracks. Or gulleys.

@{b}Smoking is bad for your health!@{ub}

@{b}Some gems harbour magical powers.@{ub}
     True--light, power, darkness, knowledge--just use them and find out.

@{b}The coin of chaos has two faces -- power and corruption.@{ub}
     The one is paid for with the other.

@{b}The Mad Minstrel harbours a dark secret.@{ub}

@{b}They say fortunes must be followed by the incantation 'in bed' to work.@{ub}
     This is only true if you're in bed at the time.

@{b}They say that a good memory might pay.@{ub}

@{b}They say that all white dragons suffer from a bad cold.@{ub}

@{b}They say that an empty stomach is one's worst enemy.@{ub}
     Always stay well fed; hunger has killed many adventurers.

@{b}They say that at times mindless rage might save your life in fights.@{ub}
     If you're getting hit anyway, go berserk and maybe you'll manage to
     kill them first.

@{b}They say that at times things can get zorky.@{ub}
     There are several Zork references in the Drakalor Chain.

@{b}They say that attacking shopkeepers is bad for your karma.@{ub}
     It could just curse you (or doom you?).

@{b}They say that being able to read is very useful when visiting the library.@{ub}
     It's the only way to take advantage of what's there.

@{b}They say that Berzio potions are useful for taming monsters.@{ub}
     They like having food items thrown their way, and this qualifies.

@{b}They say that blessed items improve one's eyesight.@{ub}

@{b}They say that blessed potions of extra-healing might be a real boon.@{ub}

@{b}They say that boozed bozos can be very helpful.@{ub}
     So give the fool some booze and find out.

@{b}They say that bugs can be really nasty.@{ub}
     Poison, swarming, and they're just gross.

@{b}They say that burning torches can be very dangerous.@{ub}
     They cause more damage than non-burning ones.

@{b}They say that champions may pray for more favours than ordinary people.@{ub}
     They sure can!

@{b}They say that companions fear darkness.@{ub}
     They tend to lose their masters.

@{b}They say that controlled teleportation is really great.@{ub}
     It is!

@{b}They say that converting an altar is difficult without losing one's faith.@{ub}
     Sometimes it wins the conversion test.

@{b}They say that corrupted things can be your boon and your doom.@{ub}

@{b}They say that cursed potions of invisibility might have strange effects.@{ub}
     They make you invisible to yourself, but not to anyone else.

@{b}They say that cursed thieves picks might do strange things.@{ub}

@{b}They say that dark elves are especially good in the night.@{ub}

@{b}They say that distortion is the way to godhood.@{ub}
     Chaos godhood only.

@{b}They say that drinking black potions during the night corrupts your soul.@{ub}
     Nah!

@{b}They say that eating beings of true evil corrupts your very essence.@{ub}
     Eating the Orb guardians corrupts your essence, not just your body
     (and so cannot be cured).

@{b}They say that eating humans is evil.@{ub}
     Or just chaotic (unlawful).

@{b}They say that eating magic-wielding monsters might be a boon for your mana.@{ub}
     They sometimes increase your mana by a point or more!

@{b}They say that elves trade strength of body for speed.@{ub}
     Eating them increases dexterity, but reduces toughness.

@{b}They say that essence of marellion moss is proof against the undead.@{ub}

@{b}They say that every coin has two sides.@{ub}

@{b}They say that excitement is a messenger of battle.@{ub}
     And if you feel excited, there's a large nest on the level.

@{b}They say that fire is the most violent element.@{ub}
     You must three times as resistant to it than other elements.

@{b}They say that gambling is bad for your finances.@{ub}
     Only if you lose; or if you win too much.

@{b}They say that gods like sacrifices of food and valuable stuff.@{ub}
     They sure don't dislike them.

@{b}They say that good gamblers know which coins they have to use.@{ub}

@{b}They say that graveyards are dangerous places.@{ub}
     You can lose strength, toughness, or life!

@{b}They say that greater vaults are hiding places for artifacts.@{ub}
     Frequently they have a named creature and an artifact in them.

@{b}They say that green pools contain deadly slime.@{ub}

@{b}They say that herb bushes grow according to magical patterns.@{ub}
     That old Conway magic. (See @{"Herbs" link "Herbs" 0})

@{b}They say that herbs have strange effects.@{ub}
     Each has its own strange effect.

@{b}They say that hobbits don't like shoes.@{ub}
     It reduces their dexterity.

@{b}They say that holy water might bear fruits.@{ub}
     Try using it on an herb plant.

@{b}They say that Infinity does not permit to visit any place twice.@{ub}
     Levels are generated randomly, and you can never go back.

@{b}They say that it is not wise to leave one's cause after being crowned to be
a champion.@{ub}
     The god who crowned you will find a punishment.

@{b}They say that it might be useful to remain persistent with uncharged wands.@{ub}
     Eventually they will work once more.

@{b}They say that it might come in handy to discover a use for useless potions.@{ub}
     There is a use for them, but not until late in the game; you will be
     rewarded.

@{b}They say that Khelavaster is still alive.@{ub}
     He is; it's just a matter of time until you find him.

@{b}They say that kicking a stuck door helps.@{ub}
     As long as it isn't trapped.

@{b}They say that kicking stairs helps to train your strength.@{ub}
     Well, maybe after a while.

@{b}They say that kicking stairs might be bad for your health.@{ub}
     Only if the dungeon comes crashing down on top of you.

@{b}They say that killing cats is bad for your karma.@{ub}
     It sure won't endear you to the Cat Lord.

@{b}They say that killing friends won't help you finding new ones.@{ub}

@{b}They say that libraries are especially useful for wizards.@{ub}
     More books instead of scrolls.

@{b}They say that long jumps require small moves.@{ub}

@{b}They say that many cursed items cause bad luck.@{ub}

@{b}They say that merchants are really well-spoken thieves.@{ub}

@{b}They say that monsters tamed by bards will never willingly leave.@{ub}

@{b}They say that monuments can hold dark secrets.@{ub}
     The monument to Infinity hides a Chaotic secret. And statues might
     hold less dark secrets.

@{b}They say that nobody ever heard the wail of the Banshee more than once.@{ub}
     It causes a lot of damage, usually enough to kill the first time it is
     heard.

@{b}They say that not all herbs must be eaten.@{ub}
     Some must be used, and others mixed.

@{b}They say that once you have opened the final gate there is no way back.@{ub}
     Once the four keys are used, the only way out is to win.

@{b}They say that patience is the better part of valor.@{ub}

@{b}They say that pools contain mysterious secrets.@{ub}
     But I'm not telling.

@{b}They say that potions of booze and mana-rich potions are able to charge
more than just your alcohol level.@{ub}
     Maybe they could charge where a scroll isn't available to do the job.

@{b}They say that potions of toughness tend to remove your hungry feelings.@{ub}
     They have a pretty good food value.

@{b}They say that praying at altars of your deity is helpful.@{ub}
     Yes, but not too often.

@{b}They say that quests are noble and just.@{ub}
     They increase your lawfulness.

@{b}They say that repetitive requests are frowned upon by the gods.@{ub}
     Don't bug them unless you've done enough to keep them happy.

@{b}They say that rubbing moss of mareilon onto your skin might get you moving.@{ub}
     Using it will exercise your dexterity.

@{b}They say that rusted electrical items might be dangerous to the user.@{ub}
     Heh heh, try zapping a rusty wand of lightning.

@{b}They say that sacrifices can be dangerous.@{ub}

@{b}They say that shopkeepers sometimes try to cheat the customer.@{ub}

@{b}They say that shops are dangerous at night.@{ub}

@{b}They say that Sis might enhance your creativity.@{ub}
     There are several ways to use them to your benefit; maybe you'll find
     another.

@{b}They say that skeletons like bones.@{ub}
     Try giving one one.

@{b}They say that smashing statues might yield magical wands.@{ub}
     If you're lucky.

@{b}They say that some items are useful when worn shortly before special
moments.@{ub}

@{b}They say that some statues have magical bones.@{ub}
     Wands.

@{b}They say that some wands are not very reliable.@{ub}
     Like wonder and ball lightening.

@{b}They say that the ancient dwarf knows a lot about quests.@{ub}
     Just ask him!

@{b}They say that the banshee transformed after losing her beloved husband.@{ub}
     And so she might be transformed again by another husband.

@{b}They say that the cat lord finds no fault with ye if ye never harmed any
cat.@{ub}
     In fact, he rewards you.

@{b}They say that the dungeons of mystery consist of 100 levels.@{ub}
     Sure, but who knows where the dungeons of mystery are? These are the
     Caverns of Chaos.

@{b}They say that the forces of Law built a monument to Infinity.@{ub}
     But it has been corrupted, and is now the infinite dungeon.

@{b}They say that the gods do not yearn for material wealth.@{ub}
     They don't know what they're talking about.

@{b}They say that the gods greatly favour living sacrifices.@{ub}
     Greatly.

@{b}They say that the great rift is very dangerous for almost everyone.@{ub}
     Very true.

@{b}They say that the guild of industrious brutal muggers writes really
confusing manuals.@{ub}
     Just read one and see, but backup first.

@{b}They say that the home of the banshee is ruled by eternal decay.@{ub}
     Actually, things never seem to decay on her level. Use it as a meat
     locker.

@{b}They say that the king hid a lot of gold in these dungeons.@{ub}
     Good thing he left a Royal Guard.

@{b}They say that the library charges high fees.@{ub}

@{b}They say that the mint-flavored juice distilled out of morgia roots
improves stamina, slakes thirst and conceals bad breath.@{ub}
     Toughness and wisdom.

@{b}They say that the radiance of chaos will corrupt you the faster the deeper
you descend.@{ub}
     Depth accelerates the process even more.

@{b}They say that the secret to becoming a Chaos God is hidden in the Drakalor
Chain.@{ub}
     In pieces in various places, yes.

@{b}They say that there are many gems deep under the mountains.@{ub}

@{b}They say that there is a secret level guarded by many powerful monsters
which contains several artifacts.@{ub}

@{b}They say that thick gauntlets are great for isolating your hands.@{ub}
     Isolating them from, say, other things. Use against poison hands.

@{b}They say that those who have too many friends also have too many enemies.@{ub}

@{b}They say that those who hear the wail of the banshee are doomed.@{ub}
     It does lots of damage, but doesn't doom.

@{b}They say that those, who manage to empty a pool, will receive a wish.@{ub}
     Only if they're extremely lucky.

@{b}They say that tiny caves can be very large.@{ub}
     Yes, they can.

@{b}They say that to be a champion of one's cause is very valuable when using
ancient magic.@{ub}
     Artifacts are tiring to use, but less so for champions.

@{b}They say that too much chaos essence corrupts thy inner self.@{ub}
     Don't eat it!

@{b}They say that true berserkers fight naked.@{ub}
     They also die young, but what the heck!

@{b}They say that using artifacts costs a lot of energy.@{ub}
     You'll need to eat more to compensate. Using some of them corrupts.

@{b}They say that wands of knocking might split your skull.@{ub}
     Or the skull of another.

@{b}They say that when you hear a "Hurumph!" you'd better start to run.@{ub}
     Because things that make that noise can be very dangerous.

@{b}They say that you might find gems on the deep levels.@{ub}

@{b}They say that you need a strong will to enter the great rift.@{ub}
     At least 20, much higher to not fall.

@{b}They say that you need to be an expert climber to survive the great rift.@{ub}
     100 climbing, minimum.

@{b}They say that you need to be very experienced to enter the great rift.@{ub}
     At least level 18.

@{b}They say that you only can be the champion of your deity if you are very
close to your deity.@{ub}
     Extremely close would be more accurate.

@{b}They say that you should not slow down in your final fight.@{ub}
     But the creatures there will try to slow you.

@{b}They say that you should seek the heart of the mountains.@{ub}

@{b}They say that you should try to investigate the potential uses of beewax.@{ub}
     It can be very useful.

@{b}They say that you should wish for appearance.@{ub}

@{b}They say that you should wish for charisma.@{ub}

@{b}They say that you should wish for dexterity.@{ub}

@{b}They say that you should wish for friends.@{ub}

@{b}They say that you should wish for knowledge.@{ub}

@{b}They say that you should wish for mana.@{ub}

@{b}They say that you should wish for strength.@{ub}

@{b}They say that you should wish for toughness.@{ub}

@{b}They say that you should wish for wealth.@{ub}

@{b}They say that you should wish for willpower.@{ub}

@{b}They say that you should wish for wishes.@{ub}
     Only the foolish do this.

@{b}They say that you will feel the corrupting incursions of Chaos.@{ub}
     Far too soon.

@{b}They say that you will need a weapon of mass destruction to come closer to
your goal.@{ub}
     It certainly helps.

@{b}They say that your piety depends on your disposition towards all gods of
your pantheon.@{ub}
     If you can keep all the gods of your pantheon happy, your score will
     reflect it.

@{b}They say ye cannot shoot yourself, no matter how hard ye try.@{ub}
     I've managed (but only with magic).

@{b}This cookie will make you pay a high price.@{ub}
    This is a joke.

@{b}Those of Trollish Blood must drink from the Bloody Pool.@{ub}

@{b}Those who guard artifacts are deadly enemies.@{ub}
     Only if they see you.

@{b}To be heavy is not very nift in a deep rift.@{ub}
     Not very nifty, indeed.

@{b}To leave the animated forest you will have to reach the corner opposite of
the entrance.@{ub}
     True.

@{b}Ye dost not need to find some kind of amulet to save the world.@{ub}
     True.

@{b}Your termination is long due.@{ub}
     Uh oh.

