@node "People" "A Who's Who Of The Chain"

@{b}Terinyo, the village@{ub}

@{b}Munxip the shopkeeper.@{ub} The easiest food source in the beginning.

@{b}Twyat Pare the Sheriff.@{ub} Great for helping lawful character along the way, he
offers two quests. The first is to kill the Raider leader, Kranach, but
will be voided if not completed before the character reaches level 6
(Kranach is no idiot). The second is to bring Hotzenplotz, the Crime lord,
to justice (a completely lawful act if he's already hostile). The first
quests yields 3000 gold, the second an amulet of order. If both are
completed, the Sheriff will teach the Law skill. He gives a 100 gold bounty
for raider corpses, 50-75 for outlaws. He is also the object of a quest
from Hotzenplotz.

@{b}Guth'Alak the Druid.@{ub} Source of a quest to kill Keethrax, a corrupted Druid.
This quest and the elder's quest are mutually exclusive. Also provides a
quest to help the Greater White Unicorn to characters of level 30 or
greater. If given the corpse of a greater chaos creature, he will reward
you with a potion of cure corruption.

@{b}Blup the baby water dragon.@{ub} Will teach the swimming skill if given enough
potions of carrot juice. Finding his mother and telling him her location
will eventually yield the artifact, the runed trident.

@{b}Yggaz the fool.@{ub} Full of rumors, he also trades random potions when given
potions of booze.

@{b}Rynt the village elder.@{ub} Source of the quest to relieve the carpenter, which
is exclusive of the Druid's quest. Completion of the quest yields rewards
from the Carpenter, and reduced prices at the market.

@{b}Yrrigs the Carpenter.@{ub} Crazed by the Village Dungeon, he is the object of the
quest from the elder. Only found here if the quest i speacefully completed.
He can be killed or peacefully rescued, which results
in the healing skill from the healer in the village dungeon for
non-chaotics. His death yields a book of bridge building and a hatchet; his
peaceful rescue also yields a potion of rust removal. He can also verbally
teach/improve bridge building, if sane.


@{b}Lawenilothehl, the outlaw settlement@{ub}

@{b}Barnabas the shopkeeper.@{ub}

@{b}Yergius the Master Thief.@{ub} Teaches pick pocket skill to non-lawfuls, and
teaches several other skills to members of the thieves' guild (climbing,
stealth, pick pockets, open locks, detect traps, disarm traps).

@{b}Hotzenplotz the crime lord.@{ub} Quest to kill the Sheriff yields an amulet of
chaos. If you've not taken the Druid's quest, he'll ask you to kill the
healer, giving you the elder's quest to rescue the carpenter. If you
complete this quest, he'll make an appointment for you with the mad doctor.
He is the object of a Sheriff's quest.

@{b}Grunge and Munge the half-orc bouncers.@{ub} They just guard Hotzenplotz, and are
amazing conversationalists.

@{b}Shriek the cloaked ratling.@{ub} He'll sell you keys.

@{b}Kranf Niest the mad doctor.@{ub} If you complete Hotzenplotz's quest to kill the
healer, Kranf will teach you the healing skill (at the expense of some
Learning and Willpower, while removing any helmet you are wearing), or give
you a stethoscope if you already know healing.


@{b}in the underwater cave@{ub}

@{b}Shyssiryxius the female great water dragon.@{ub} This is Blup's Mom. Chat with
her and then return to Chat with Blup and send him on his way home and
eventually you'll get the artifact "the rune-covered trident."

@{b}in the village dungeon@{ub}

@{b}Yrrigs the Carpenter.@{ub} (as in Terinyo) He's mad at this point, so either kill
him or lead him up to the healer to be cured.

@{b}Jharod the healer.@{ub} If you are merciful and non-chaotic, he will teach you
the healing skill and give you a stethoscope. Healing injured monsters or
leading the carpenter to him to be healed count as merciful acts.


@{b}in the high mountain village@{ub}

@{b}??? the shopkeeper.@{ub} He sells and buys stuff.

@{b}??? the Ogre guard.@{ub} He guards the gaol; not its contents, just the building.

@{b}Hawkslayer.@{ub} He's a companion for non-chaotics who reach a certain level and
can give him the password (iceberg).

@{b}Baay'Gaab the old crone.@{ub} She's useless for non-chaotics. She assigns various
quests for others, starting with the satisfaction of the demented ratling.
Then a giant boar skull, a potion of cure corruption, a farmer corpse, a
scroll of danger... She'll eventually give you the Medal of Chaos, part of
the trinity for becoming a Chaos God.

@{b}the nefarious doctor.@{ub} He has a pricey flesh golem for sale.

@{b}the oracle.@{ub} She'll only talk to one who is ready to become a chaos god (have
all three artifacts of chaos--the sceptre, the medal, and the crown) and is
ready to dive.

@{b}in the Pyramid@{b}

@{b}Rehetep the mummy lord.@{ub} He grants a challenge when the charater reaches
level 13; the offer is closed at level 17. He wears two artifacts, the
ancient mummy wrapping and the ankh. Vulnerable to flames.

@{b}in Dark Forge@{ub}

@{b}Kherab the dwarven artificer.@{ub} He offers highly chaotic quests with artifact
rewards that corrupt the user. Kill the village Druid for the shield of raw
steel, the dwarven elder for the amulet of raw steel. There's a spear of
raw steel, too, but I've never gotten it (not sure it's coded in as
attainable). He holds an anvil, a great hammer, and a decent heavy
crossbow.

@{b}in the Tower of Fire@{ub}

@{b}the Ancient Chaos Wyrm.@{ub} Holds the Orb of Elemental Fire

@{b}at the Minstrel's hut@{ub}

@{b}the Mad Minstrel.@{ub} Will sing to you lots of hints that are really helpful
unless you've already learned about them through some silly spoilers files.

@{b}in the Great Library@{ub}

@{b}the librarian.@{ub} Well, he doesn't say much.

@{b}in the peaceful glade@{ub}

@{b}the old Barbarian.@{ub} After achieving level 13, he'l assign non-chaotics a
quest to kill 20 of the first monster you killed. When you do it, he
teaches you the Courage skill.

@{b}in the green glade@{ub}

@{b}Riurri the Greater White Unicorn.@{ub} He appears after talking to the village
Druid after level 30. He'll ask you to kill the Greater Black Unicorn; if
you do, he'll cleanse you of all corruptions, but only once.


@{b}in the corrupt glade@{ub}

@{b}???? the Greater Black Unicorn.@{ub} He'll ask you to kill the Greater White
Unicorn; if you do, he'll corrupt you and give you 7 potions of gain
attribute.

@{b}in the Dwarven graveyard@{ub}

@{b}(the undead dwarven chaos berserker) Griff Bloodaxe.@{ub} Put him out of his
misery either by killing him, or 'U'sing a potion of holy water on his
grave.

@{b}Nonnak the Necromancer.@{ub} He raised Griff and all the others in the area. He
keeps his artifact sword in Griff's grave and the artifact the elemental
gauntlets in a hidden nook on the east side of the room.

@{b}in the Caverns of Chaos@{ub}

@{b}in the Arena{ub}

@{b}the arena master.@{ub} He grants you access to the arena and upon your 20th win
gives you the artifact the Golden Gladius.
the possible Champions to face: @{b}Bonk the Hill Giant, Li-Hon-Kay the Ogre
Magus, Ripclaw the Troll berserker, Spardakius the Minotaur.@{ub}

@{b}in Dwarftown@{ub}

@{b}Thrundarr the Dwarven elder.@{ub} He assigns several quests, each with their own
rewards. If you complete a quest before he assigns it, he'll just give you
another random monster quest instead. His first is to kill a random
monster, but the reward is the potion of literacy for non-literate
characters, or identifying your entire inventory for others. Next is the
quest to find the other side of the animated forest, which yields a wand of
fireball. Then vanquishing the neighboring Ogre tribe for 5000 gold. Then
becoming Champion of the Arena (or another random monster quest if you're
already champion) which grants you the artifact shield Rolf's Savior.
Finally killing a daemon attacking the village to get the artifact Big
Punch. You should also ask about the "portal", which will give the separate
quest to free the soul of Griff Bloodaxe. He can answer questions about all
of the following: shop, waldenbrook, traits, gart, innkeeper, torgall,
gladiator, grizzelled, smith, glod, mace, hammer, axe, ogre, orc, gold,
khelevaster, sage, corruption, chaos, caladriel, phial, king, high,
ancient, bloodaxe, griff, portal, gate, banshee, greet, hello, groro,
gorko, sis, si, rolf, dwarven, dwarf, city, guest.

@{b}Waldenbrook the shopkeeper.@{ub} Again, he sells and buys stuff. He occassionally
manages to stock an artifact or other really great item.

@{b}the priest.@{ub} He's of your race and can be chatted for information if your
alignment matches his. The town is quite loyal to him, as is his god, so
treat with caution or his ghost just might haunt you.

@{b}Garth, the dwarven weapon master.@{ub} Chat with him to buy training from him. I
pay him between 90 and 200 times the current skill I'm trying to improve,
which seems to work up to 18 or 19, and then just gets annoying (but I
over-tip at restaurants, too).

@{b}Glod, the dwarven smith.@{ub} He can teach you smithing, but the price depends on
your appearance. He can also fix broken items and remove the rust from
anything you're not wearing (for a price).

@{b}Bart, the grizzled gladiator.@{ub} He has a few tales about his days, but is most
useful if you give him the Golden Gladius. He'll increase your weapon
knowledge and teach you any fighting skills you are lacking
({(Learning)d10} skill points in all melee weapons, backstabbing, find
weakness?, tactics, two-weapon combat).

@{b}Torgall, the barkeeper.@{ub} He has heard all kinds of rumors.

@{b}the dwarven mystic.@{ub} If you aren't chaotic or doomed, he'll give you the
artifact Rolf's Companion. You have to teleport into his room, though, and
out again.

@{b}the demented ratling.@{ub} He will give chaotics a quest for 6 artifacts. If
completed, he'll reveal the method for getting one part of the trinity for
becoming a Chaos God. ("Listen, blob. Visit da ancient stone circle in da
middle of da darkest night. Den ya'll find ze entrance to a part of dat
trinity. Originally it wuz built for all da alignments... ...and it
prubably haz zume other special effex. But we are gonna uze it for us
means, aye?" The demented ratling winks at you. "Get da part of ze trinity
and try to win ze price.")

@{b}Khelavaster, the dying scholar.@{ub} He's the one who inspired you to start this
journey. Kill him or talk to him. He has a few things to say about how to
close the Chaos Gate. His equipment is fairly consistant (boots of dex,
amulet of defense/protection).

@{b}the Eternal Guardian.@{ub} You must have the Ring of the High Kings to pass him
peacefully. You can try to kill him, but be prepared to do it again.

@{b}in the Casino@{ub}

@{b}???? the shopkeeper.@{ub} He sells, but does not buy. There is usually at least
one artifact in the shop, and several other goodies. Try picking up
everything interesting, expensive, or unidentified and reading a blessed
scroll of identify. Or you could win enough in the casino to buy what you
want.

@{b}the big casino guard.@{ub} The big guard is substantially tougher than the
others.

@{b}the Snake from Beyond.@{ub} Holds the Orb of Elemental Water.

@{b}Bugs the Bunny Master.@{ub} Leader of the bunny level.

@{b}the Cat Lord.@{ub} If you've never killed a cat, chat with him to get your
reward, the artifact the ring of the Master Cat; otherwise prepare to be
attacked.

@{b}Yuglash, the Master Summoner.@{ub} Holds the Orb of Elemental Air.

@{b}the Ancient Stone Beast.@{ub} Holds the Orb of Elemental Earth.

@endnode

